The article discusses the commemoration of the Meds Yeghern, a mass atrocity in which 1.5 million Armenians were deported, massacred, or died during the final years of the Ottoman Empire. It emphasizes the strong ties between the American and Armenian peoples and acknowledges the humanitarian support provided by the American Committee for Armenian and Syrian Relief in 1915. The article also praises the resilience and contributions of the Armenian people to the United States. It mentions the importance of acknowledging and reckoning with the painful history between Armenians and Turks, and reaffirms the commitment to protecting vulnerable religious and ethnic minorities worldwide.